{% macro render_naming_checklist(language) -%}
#### Naming Conventions Checklist

{% if language == 'python' -%}
```
Python Naming Checklist:
- [ ] All filenames use snake_case (my_module.py, not MyModule.py)
- [ ] All classes use PascalCase (UserService, not user_service)
- [ ] All functions/methods use snake_case (get_user, not getUser)
- [ ] Private methods start with _ (_internal_method)
- [ ] Dunder methods have __ on both sides (__init__, not _init_)
- [ ] Constants are in configuration files, not module-level
- [ ] Variable names are clear (user_count, not uc)
- [ ] Boolean variables start with is_ or has_ (is_active, has_permission)
- [ ] Database tables use snake_case
- [ ] Environment variables use UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- [ ] No single-letter variables except in loops (for i in range(n))
- [ ] Type hints use T | None (not Optional[T])
```

{% elif language == 'typescript' -%}
```
TypeScript Naming Checklist:
- [ ] All filenames use kebab-case (user-service.ts, not UserService.ts)
- [ ] All classes use PascalCase (UserService, not user_service)
- [ ] All functions/variables use camelCase (getUser, not get_user)
- [ ] All interfaces start with I or end with able (IUserService, Serializable)
- [ ] All types use PascalCase (UserRole, ApiResponse)
- [ ] All enums use PascalCase values (UserRole.Admin, not UserRole.ADMIN)
- [ ] Constants use UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (API_TIMEOUT, MAX_RETRIES)
- [ ] Component files use PascalCase (UserForm.tsx, NavBar.tsx)
- [ ] Hook files use camelCase (useAuth.ts, useFetch.ts)
- [ ] Boolean variables start with is, has, or can (isActive, hasPermission)
- [ ] Private fields use # prefix (#privateField)
- [ ] Database columns use snake_case (user_id, created_at)
```

